# Line-ending and binary handling.
#
# History: installer/thresholds.iss is auto-generated by
# build_thresholds_iss.py with explicit CRLF (newline="\r\n"). The repo
# originally stored .iss files as LF, producing a recurring phantom-diff
# on every git operation when core.autocrlf=true converts working-tree
# files in place. This file pins the .iss extension to CRLF in both
# repo and working tree to match the build script's intent — Inno Setup
# is Windows-only, so CRLF is the native expectation.
#
# All other text files default to LF in repo. Binaries are explicit.

# Default: autodetect text vs binary; text files stored as LF in repo
* text=auto eol=lf

# Inno Setup — CRLF in repo and working tree (matches Windows tooling)
*.iss text eol=crlf

# Binaries — explicit, prevent any line-ending munging
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.bmp   binary
*.ico   binary
*.gif   binary
*.wav   binary
*.mp3   binary
*.ogg   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.zip   binary
*.tar.gz binary
*.tgz   binary
*.exe   binary
*.dll   binary
*.so    binary
*.pyc   binary
*.onnx  binary
*.pt    binary
*.bin   binary
